tourBios.curYearHigh: Finished T16 at the PGA Professional National Championship, earning a spot in the PGA Championship in August at Whistling Straits. Made a hole-in-one in July on No. 3 during a practice round at Whistling Straits.

tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Was the runner-up at the Northern Texas PGA Section Championship.

1997: Missed the cut in both of his European Tour starts, including The Open Championship.

Amateur: Was a member of Great Britain and Ireland's 1997 Walker Cup team, finishing 3-1-0 in his four matches. Played alongside teammate Justin Rose in GB&I's 18-6 loss to the United States at Quaker Ridge GC in Scarsdale, N.Y. Was the only member of his team to win a singles' match on the final day. Defeated Joel Kribel, 2 and 1, after dispatching Duke Delcher, 5 and 4, earlier in the competition.
tourBios.personal: Head professional at Midland CC in Midland, Texas, former site of a Web.com Tour event...Has 13 holes-in-one to his credit and a double eagle.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA TOUR was T60th in 2000 at the Doral-Ryder Open.
